channel.title: Keys for PC games
channel.description: A few years ago I bought Halo CE for my computer. When I moved a while ago I lost the game, but found it a couple weeks ago when I was cleaning my basement. I just loaded it up, (on a new computer by the way. I have no idea where the other one is), and it's asking me for the product key. Is there any way I can get by without the key since I already put it in once for this disk? Any help is appreciated.

item.title: Keys for PC games
item.dc:creator: @vManlyMan vManlyMan
item.description:
@vManlyMan wrote:

Lin:

Either restart your computer if the “file is in use”, or make some space. If I remember correctly, I think Halo CE takes up like 7GB. I’m probably wrong, but that’s just what I remember.

Restarted it and nothing happened. And it says I have enough space to do it on the previous screen, but stops at 1% and gives the error I mentioned earlier.
